  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH Intervention to Support Drought-affected Populations of Samburu County, Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Mothers are trained on safe hygiene practices to increase Hygiene Water Treatment and Storage (HWTS) knowledge and are equipped with items for water treatment, storage, carriage and personal hygiene.

2. Facilitation of community meetings to increase HWTS knowledge of the commmunity,especially men. The sessions are interactive and participatory, with the ACTED hygiene promoter encouraging audience demonstration of good hand-washing techniques, eliciting participant&#x2019;s feedback and questions.

3. Radio spots aired on local radio station in Samburu County to increase awareness on HWTS through listening to radio spots whose content focus on hygiene promotion.

4. Hygiene promotion in schools to increase hygiene practices through specifically modified hygiene promotion training and distribution of basic hygiene kits.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reducing malnutrition rates by improving hygiene practices and access to safe and clean water for affected beneficiary women, girls, boys and men in Samburu North and Samburu East Districts.</narrative>
  </description>
